Poor nutritional status and malnutrition are prevalent for patients undergoing treatment for head and neck cancer.

 Inadequate dietary intake is multi factorial, with patients experiencing dysphagia and or anorexia caused by various cancer treatments.

 Current standard practice utilizes Gastrostomy Tube placement to manage adverse nutritional effects related to Head and Neck cancer treatment.

